---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SkillsGrid from '../components/SkillsGrid.astro';
import ScrollReveal from '../components/ScrollReveal.astro';
import { selectedMedia } from '../data/resume';

const press = selectedMedia.filter((m) => m.type === 'press');
const viz = selectedMedia.filter((m) => m.type === 'visualization');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Michael Lopez, Director of Data Operations at the Child Poverty Action Lab. Turning administrative data into analysis and decisions communities can act on."
>
  <div class="border-t-4 border-cool">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 lg:py-16">

      <!-- 2-col editorial hero -->
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:gap-12 lg:gap-16 mb-12 lg:mb-16">
        <!-- Bio (md: left, mobile: below headshot) -->
        <ScrollReveal class="order-2 md:order-1 md:flex-1 md:min-w-0 mt-10 md:mt-0">
          <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Hi, I'm Michael</h1>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              I lead data operations at the <a href="https://childpovertyactionlab.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Child Poverty Action Lab</a>,
              a backbone organization for nonprofits across North Texas. CPAL works on the things that actually
              change child poverty in Dallas: public safety, maternal health, benefits delivery,
              housing, and criminal justice. As Director, Data Operations, I run the data engineering team, our
              data platform (Databricks, AI-enabled workflows), and the internal tools that put data in front
              of non-technical staff and partner orgs.
            </p>
            <p>
              It took a few detours to get here. My first real job was coordinating a child development lab
              at UT Dallas, and the part that stuck with me wasn't the research itself, it was sitting with
              the parents of our young participants and trying to explain what we'd found. The gap between
              how researchers talk to each other and how findings actually reach the people who can do
              something with them turned out to be the thread of my career. It pulled me through a policy
              internship at <a href="https://childrenatrisk.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Children at Risk</a>,
              an MPP at UT Dallas, and into CPAL in 2020.
            </p>
            <p>
              Two convictions sit underneath the work. First: <strong>public data is only useful when the
              people closest to a problem can act on it</strong>, and most of the data that could help families
              is still locked up in formats and systems that field-team workers, community organizations, and
              decision-makers can't reach. Second: <strong>nonprofits deserve the same data infrastructure as
              the institutions and markets they're often working against.</strong> Most of what I do, at CPAL
              and outside of it, is in service of those two ideas.
            </p>
          </div>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <!-- Headshot + role chip + status (md: right, mobile: top) -->
        <ScrollReveal class="order-1 md:order-2 md:w-60 md:shrink-0">
          <aside class="flex flex-col items-center md:items-start text-center md:text-left">
            <div class="w-44 h-44 md:w-52 md:h-52 rounded-full bg-canyon mb-5 ring-4 ring-accent/70 dark:ring-canyon/60 flex items-center justify-center" aria-label="Michael Lopez monogram placeholder">
              <span class="text-light text-6xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold tracking-tight select-none">ML</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary dark:text-dark-text">Director, Data Operations</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-cool dark:text-secondary mt-0.5 mb-4">Child Poverty Action Lab</p>
            <p class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-neutral dark:text-dark-text">
              <span class="relative flex w-2 h-2" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="absolute inset-0 rounded-full bg-secondary opacity-60 motion-safe:animate-ping"></span>
                <span class="relative w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-secondary"></span>
              </span>
              Currently in Dallas
            </p>
          </aside>
        </ScrollReveal>
      </div>

      <!-- What I'm looking for -->
      <ScrollReveal>
        <section class="rounded-xl bg-surface dark:bg-dark-surface ring-1 ring-cool/30 dark:ring-cool/40 border-l-4 border-cool p-6 sm:p-7 lg:p-8">
          <h2 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] font-semibold text-cool dark:text-secondary mb-3">What I'm looking for</h2>
          <p class="text-base lg:text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I've spent six years building the data function at the Child Poverty Action Lab from
            scratch: the analysis, the systems, and the judgment about what the numbers actually mean.
            Now I want to bring that into a larger, more established data organization, where the
            questions are harder, the data runs deeper, and the work is measured in decisions people
            make because of it. I'm looking for a data-leadership role with room to grow, one where I
            can operate at real scale and keep getting sharper about the work itself.
          </p>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Pullquote (matches case-study treatment) -->
      <ScrollReveal>
        <blockquote class="my-12 lg:my-16 sm:-mx-4 lg:-mx-12 border-l-4 border-canyon pl-6 sm:pl-8 italic font-light text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-[1.65rem] leading-snug text-primary dark:text-dark-text opacity-95 max-w-3xl">
          Public data is only useful when the people closest to a problem can act on it.
        </blockquote>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- What we've built (tinted card, numbered) -->
      <ScrollReveal>
        <section class="mt-12 lg:mt-16 p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-xl bg-accent/15 dark:bg-accent/8 ring-1 ring-accent/30 dark:ring-canyon/30">
          <h2 class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-dark-text mb-2">What we've built at CPAL</h2>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-75 mb-6 lg:mb-8 max-w-2xl">A snapshot of the work, from the decisions it informs to the infrastructure underneath.</p>

          <ol class="space-y-5 lg:space-y-6">
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">01</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">A 30+ Shiny app suite informing decisions across CPAL focus areas: housing, public safety, maternal health, benefits delivery, and criminal justice.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">02</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">An eviction data workstream feeding newly-filed cases daily to 12+ partner organizations across legal aid, advocacy, government, and academic research; the data behind <a href="https://northtexasevictions.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">North Texas Evictions</a>.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">03</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">Internal tools that let non-data staff act on data without analyst intervention, including a parcel-level outreach tool with 20 active field-team users.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">04</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">The Databricks platform migration on AWS, moving 35-40 pipelines from file-based storage onto unified cloud infrastructure with Git-tracked orchestration.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">05</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">AI workflows embedded across the team (Claude Code with custom skills and agents, MCP servers), meaningfully changing how we develop pipelines, write documentation, and review code.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-5">
              <span class="text-canyon/60 dark:text-canyon font-light tabular-nums leading-none text-2xl lg:text-3xl shrink-0 w-9">06</span>
              <span class="text-sm lg:text-base leading-relaxed">A data engineering team scaled from 1 in-house analyst to 6 external data engineers + 1 in-house data engineer, executing on the internal data roadmap.</span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Selected Media & Visualizations (inline list, hairline dividers) -->
      {selectedMedia.length > 0 && (
        <ScrollReveal>
          <section class="mt-16 lg:mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-dark-text mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class="w-8 h-0.5 bg-canyon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              Selected Media & Visualizations
            </h2>
            {press.length > 0 && (
              <div class="mb-8">
                <h3 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] font-semibold text-cool dark:text-secondary mb-3">Featured in</h3>
                <ul class="divide-y divide-accent/40 dark:divide-canyon/30">
                  {press.map((m) => (
                    <li class="py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-2">
                      <a href={m.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-medium">{m.outlet}</a>
                      <span class="opacity-75">{m.title}</span>
                      <span class="opacity-50 text-xs ml-auto">{m.date}</span>
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            )}
            {viz.length > 0 && (
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] font-semibold text-cool dark:text-secondary mb-3">Data visualizations contributed to</h3>
                <ul class="divide-y divide-accent/40 dark:divide-canyon/30">
                  {viz.map((m) => (
                    <li class="py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-2">
                      <a href={m.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-medium">{m.outlet}</a>
                      <span class="opacity-75">{m.title}</span>
                      <span class="opacity-50 text-xs ml-auto">{m.date}</span>
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            )}
          </section>
        </ScrollReveal>
      )}

      <!-- Skills (clean grid, no card wrap) -->
      <ScrollReveal>
        <section class="mt-16 lg:mt-20">
          <h2 class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-dark-text mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-8 h-0.5 bg-canyon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Technical Skills
          </h2>
          <SkillsGrid />
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <ScrollReveal>
        <section class="mt-16 lg:mt-20 text-center p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 dark:bg-accent/5 ring-1 ring-accent/30 dark:ring-canyon/30">
          <h2 class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-dark-text mb-3">Let's connect</h2>
          <p class="mb-5 text-sm max-w-md mx-auto opacity-85">
            I'm always up for talking with people building data tools for social impact.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3 text-sm">
            <a href="mailto:michael@lopezstudio.dev" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 bg-primary dark:bg-secondary text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-secondary dark:hover:bg-canyon transition-colors no-underline text-sm font-medium">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
              Email
            </a>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/michael-d-lopez" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 border-2 border-primary text-primary dark:border-dark-text dark:text-dark-text rounded-lg hover:bg-primary hover:text-white dark:hover:bg-dark-text dark:hover:text-dark-bg transition-colors no-underline text-sm font-medium">
              LinkedIn
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/lopezmichael" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2 border-2 border-primary text-primary dark:border-dark-text dark:text-dark-text rounded-lg hover:bg-primary hover:text-white dark:hover:bg-dark-text dark:hover:text-dark-bg transition-colors no-underline text-sm font-medium">
              GitHub
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
